# ▶️ How to run

```bash id="run-ocp"
chmod +x ocp-audit.sh
./ocp-audit.sh your-namespace
```

---

# 🔎 Optional (very useful in OCP)

### 1. Actual usage (not just requests/limits)

```bash id="oc-top"
oc adm top pods -n your-namespace
```

---

### 2. Include persistent volume details

```bash id="pv-details"
oc get pv | grep your-namespace
```

---

### 3. Check quotas (important in OpenShift)

```bash id="quota"
oc get resourcequota -n your-namespace
```

---

# 💡 Practical tip

OpenShift often enforces:

* **ResourceQuotas**
* **LimitRanges**

So even if a pod doesn’t define resources, defaults may still apply. If you want, I can extend the script to include those too.

